main event: A deputy sheriff observed a bright white light that hovered and then moved upwards over Cain Springs, California.
interesting points: The object's size was estimated to be similar to a weather balloon, but the nearest balloon launch was 30 miles away in El Centro.
The object was observed for 5-10 minutes.
The object hovered and then moved upwards.
The location was over Cain Springs, California.
The report was part of Project 10973, an old government UFO investigation program.
